ai:
Certainly! Here's a rap-style adaptation of the song "Meaning":

```markdown
[Chorus]
On the streets, we're pickin' up litter, keepin' it clean,
Smilin' at folks we meet, like sunshine, we beam.
But these good deeds, they settle like dust,
In the cosmic flow, they're just a momentary gust.
Are we just grindin' in vain, tell me, what's the trust?

[Bridge]
Helpin' elders cross, seats given up on the bus,
Cars halt at stripes, kindness without a fuss.
But this warmth, it's like a night sky streak,
Fades away quick, is our care just weak?
Is our concern for others just a peak, then it's bleak?

[Verse 1]
No harsh words, fixin' chairs that creak,
Freein' critters, buyin' fruits from the old and meek.
But these acts, like sands in the glass,
Slip through time, do they even last?
Are our good moves just part of the past, gone so fast?

[Verse 2]
Guidin' the lost, chattin' with kin who's alone,
Sharin' life's lessons, stories for the young sown.
But these tales, like sea foam they pop,
Touch 'em and they're gone, do they ever stop?
Are our spoken vibes just a wind's chop, then they drop?

[Verse 3]
We do extra for folks, no return we await,
Surprises we create, donate without a slate.
But these gifts, like leaves in the breeze,
Hit the ground, turn to dust with ease.
Is our generosity just a tease, not to please?

[Outro]
We do good, thinkin' we'll leave a mark,
But in the end, is it all just a lark?
'Cause humans fade, nothin' really sticks,
In this universe stage, we're just transits.
Is our existence just a mix of tricks, nothin' clicks?

[Final Verse]
But you, my friend, 'cause I see you there,
You give my actions meaning, showin' that you care.
Though destiny's fickle, the world's gonna hush,
With you, my world's bright, givin' me that rush.

la la la la la
la la la la la

[Verse 4]
But you, my friend, 'cause you're in the frame,
You make what I do feel worth the game.
Though fate's uncertain, silence will claim,
With you, my world's lit, you're my flame.

But with you, my world's bright, you're my claim to fame.

[Verse 5]
We guide the lost, talk to the lone,
Share our stories, in a gentle tone.
We give more, expectin' no throne,
Surprises we craft, donations unknown.
'Cause humans will vanish, it's widely shown,
On this cosmic stage, we're just on loan.

[Final Verse Outro]
But you, my friend, 'cause you're part of the crew,
You make what I do feel true, through and through.
la la la la la
la la la la la
